keyFacts: The subpoena demands all records from January 1, 2008 to the present for aircraft with tail numbers N750A or N722JE.
The records are sought for the criminal case United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell (20 Cr. 330 (AJN)).
Failure to comply constitutes contempt of court and may result in civil sanctions and criminal penalties.
The subpoena is issued by the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York, signed by Audrey Strauss.
The aircraft records are being sought from Insured Aircraft Title Service, LLC, an aircraft title service company based in Oklahoma City.
